**Description** 




 We currently have a vacancy for a
 **Solution Architect** 
 fluent in English, to offer his/her services as an expert who will be based in Stockholm, Sweden. The work will be carried out either in the company’s premises or on site at customer premises. In the context of the first assignment, the successful candidate will be integrated in the Development team of the company that will closely cooperate with a major client’s IT team on site.










**Your tasks** 









* Support the development and implementation of long-term strategies in the required domain (business process, information, application and technology);
* Define and design as-is and to-be models for the domain;
* Define and develop architecture frameworks, concepts and methods;
* Facilitate development work with architecture support;
* Communicate and explain architecture deliverables;
* Create and maintain models in Sparx Enterprise Architect (or other tools);
* Ensure incorporation of security by design;
* Develop and maintain a comprehensive record of usability requirements and develop relevant IT Products.









**Requirements** 









* University degree with minimum 6 years of experience in IT or non university degree with minimum 12 years of experience in IT;
* Minimum 3 years of experience in enterprise architecture or domain architectures (business process, information, application and technology);
* Experience with Business Information Systems such as PRIME, ECMP, PHE Intranet;
* Experience with SharePoint Online, Power Platform,Power BI and Azure;
* Experience with DevOps practices, CI/CD and automation, as well as programming/ scripting experience;
* Experience in the application of enterprise architecture frameworks and methods (TOGAF);
* Experience in modelling languages and concepts, such as ArchiMate;
* Experience using relevant IT architecture tools, such as Sparx Enterprise Architect;
* Knowledge of design patterns in big data, cloud solutions (Azure) and artificial intelligence and knowledge in public health would be considered an asset;
* A TOGAF (The Open Group Architecture Framework), SABSA (Sherwood Applied Business Security Architecture) or ArchiMate Certification will be considered an asset;
* Excellent command of the English language.



 # Urgent Requirement

**Description & Requirements**
 Electronic Arts creates next-level entertainment experiences that inspire players and fans around the world. Here, everyone is part of the story. Part of a community that connects across the globe. A place where creativity thrives, new perspectives are invited, and ideas matter. A team where everyone makes play happen.




 Most companies call it HR. But at Electronic Arts, we made the deliberate decision to brand our organization People Experience (PE). PE is not just a play on words: it’s a team of cultural stewards who carefully create programs and talent strategies that directly impact our teams’ experience. For the better. We allow our People to achieve the most meaningful work of their careers.




 We’re responsible for recruiting the best and most diverse talent on the planet. But it doesn’t stop there. We also support their growth through learning programs, internal mobility, affinity group participation, and leadership development. We listen to our employees and dive into analytics to anchor our recommendations and decisions to keep engagement high. Last but not least, we’re responsible for a total rewards strategy that incentivizes equitably, pr




 Will report to Senior Director People Partnership Europe. This role is based at our Stockholm office, Hybrid.




**Responsibilities**
 What the
 **Director, People Partnerships** 
 does at EA:




* You will develop partnerships with business leaders, People Experience leaders and management across client group(s) throughout Sweden and Finland to support a wide range of people related activities that support delivery of business strategy and goals, including leadership capability, performance management and team effectiveness;
* You will provide leadership and oversight to your team as they prepare for, manage and communicate the cyclical programs including: compensation planning, performance, talent and succession planning, team engagement surveys and action planning;
* You will lead a team of People Partner professionals to ensure consistent and streamlined practices and services across the business;
* You will analyze workforce data across the BU and designated site and people metrics to improve the worker experience, assess gaps and opportunities and provides insights to help inform the right decisions;
* You will support our ability to change by developing the capacity and readiness for change across the business/region and facilitates change plans for client group(s) including coaching management on planning and communications and ensuring change acceptance and sustainability;
* You will support the ongoing development and career progression of team members through coaching, performance feedback and career discussion to foster meaningful career experiences while meeting the needs of the business;
* You will work with managers, employees and COEs to respond to employee relations issues and develop overall capability to foster a healthy, cohesive, collaborative, fun and fair workplace.
* You will enable Site Governance to ensure leadership collaboration across designated sites. Is an active member of site governance in the Stockholm Location.
* Country Role - You will be responsible for ensuring that People Policies and Practices are kept up to date to mitigate risk and remain compliant in partnership with People Policy Excellence and Legal. You will review and approve exception requests across BU's to ensure consistency and compliance with country laws and fair treatment. Partner with legal to ensure changes to country employment laws and legislation are understood by the team. Escalates country risk concerns in a timely manner to Senior Director, People Practices Europe.
* You will be a subject matter expert in local CBAs/Unions relationships, serves as an escalation point to the team on more complex matters. You will partner with PPE team and legal on CBA, Unions and labour law matters. Stakeholder in all responses/decisions as it relates to Union relationships. You will be a key stakeholder managing the relation with the Unions.


**Qualifications**
* You have a Bachelor’s degree in a relevant field combined with over 15 years’ progressive experience as an HR business partner and manager;
* Ability to think strategically, execute tactically, and collaborate across regional and global stakeholder groups;
* Comfort in speaking truth to power;
* Proven experience using data and data-driven insights to support the business;
* Builder of HR solutions based on best practices, and an astute business member who employs solutions that affect the current and future performance of the business;
* Subject matter expert, with demonstrated experience in coaching and development, change management, and overall talent management;
* Strong change management skills - able to navigate complex problems, evaluate the options and partner to achieve the best business results.
* Outstanding project leadership and delivery experience; overseeing region-wide, high impact talent programs across the business;
* Experience with regional/local employment legislation combined with the ability to gain a high-level understanding of regional employment customs and practices;
* Has experience creating healthy organizations, driving transformation and helping culture be a competitive advantage.


**About Electronic Arts**
 We’re proud to have an extensive portfolio of games and experiences, locations around the world, and opportunities across EA. We value adaptability, resilience, creativity, and curiosity. From leadership that brings out your potential, to creating space for learning and experimenting, we empower you to do great work and pursue opportunities for growth.




 We take a holistic approach with our benefits program, focusing on physical, emotional, financial, career, and community wellness to support a balanced life with paid time off and new parent leave, plus free games and so much more. We nurture environments where our teams can always bring their best to what they do.




 Electronic Arts is an equal opportunity employer. All employment decisions are made without regard to race, color, national origin, ancestry, sex, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, age, genetic information, religion, disability, medical condition, pregnancy, marital status, family status, veteran status, or any other characteristic protected by law. We will also consider employment qualified applicants with criminal records in accordance with applicable law. EA also makes workplace accommodations for qualified individuals with disabilities as required by applicable law.
